# Environment Variables

This project uses environment variables for configuration. Copy this file to `.env` and fill in your values.

## EmailJS Configuration

Required for the contact form to work:

```env
PUBLIC_EMAILJS_SERVICE_ID=your_service_id_here
PUBLIC_EMAILJS_TEMPLATE_ID=your_template_id_here
PUBLIC_EMAILJS_PUBLIC_KEY=your_public_key_here
```

To get these values:
1. Sign up at [EmailJS](https://www.emailjs.com/)
2. Create an email service
3. Create an email template
4. Copy the Service ID, Template ID, and Public Key from your dashboard

## Umami Analytics

Required for website analytics:

```env
PUBLIC_UMAMI_WEBSITE_ID=your_website_id_here
```

To get this value:
1. Sign up at [Umami Cloud](https://umami.is/)
2. Create a new website
3. Copy the Website ID from your dashboard

## Development vs Production

- Analytics only loads when `import.meta.env.PROD` is `true`
- During development (`npm run dev`), analytics will not load
- During production builds (`npm run build`), analytics will be included

## Security Note

All environment variables use the `PUBLIC_` prefix, which makes them available in the browser. This is necessary for client-side functionality like EmailJS and analytics.
